<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="delight-n">delight <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /dɪ'laɪt/    美 /dɪ'laɪt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-u">1.★ <strong>[U] 快乐；高兴</strong></h4>
<p>great pleasure：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The children were screaming <strong>in</strong> / <strong>with delight</strong>. 
孩子们高兴得尖叫。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She is a kind-hearted lady with a positive attitude toward life because she <strong>takes delight in</strong> helping others.
她是一个热心善良、积极面对人生的女士，因为她助人为乐。</p><footer>2014 天津改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Li Na won the game easily, <strong>to the delight of</strong> all her fans.
李娜轻松赢得比赛，让她所有的球迷很高兴。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>To his</strong> great <strong>delight</strong>, his novel was accepted for publication. 
使他极为高兴的是，他的小说被接受出版了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2c">2.<strong>[C] 令人高兴的事：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Bedtime stories are one of <strong>the delights of</strong> early childhood. 
睡前故事是儿时的一大乐趣。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It is a delight to</strong> see my parents so fit and healthy. 
看到父母身体这么健康我真高兴。</p></div></div>